HEADWORD: Calipee
<hw>Cal"i*pee</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Calipash</er>]</ety> <def>A part of a turtle which is attached to
the lower shell. It contains a fatty and gelatinous substance of a light
yellowish color, much esteemed as a delicacy.</def>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

